properties.description: Restaurant, does not have a customer-only sign. Otherwise just ask politely for water. The water is very good.
A small man made cave. Dusty floor and space for about 3 people with mats.
One room with intact roof. No door nor windows, open. Dusty concrete floor. Space for up to 8 people.
The hut is locked with two massive locks. The rest are basic huts, two with mostly intact roofs.

Two of the ruins have mostly intact roofs. They are open otherwise. There are some wooden plankets which can be used as ground cover for mattresses. 3-4 people. The hut 880 m southwest is better suited for overnighting and as shelter though.
A ruin with mostly intact roof. No facilities, just dusty ground floor. A few wooden plankets.
